#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:445
msgid "Source"
msgstr "Bron"

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:452
msgid ""
"On the left of the track head the green vertical lines (V1 or A2). The"
" green line is connected to the source clip in the project bin. Only when"
" a clip is selected in the project bin, the green line shows up depending"
" on the type of the clip (A/V clip, picture/title/color clip, audio clip)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:457
msgid "Target"
msgstr "Doel"

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:464
msgid ""
"In the track head the target V1 or A1 is active when it’s yellow. An"
" active target track reacts to edit operations like insert a clip even if"
" the source is not active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:467
msgid "**The concept is like thinking of connectors**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/editing.rst:469
msgid ""
"Connect the source (the clip in the project bin) to a target (a track in"
" the timeline). Only when both connectors on the **same** track are"
